[SN]TITLE[SN]
Noel Hunt & Adam Buxton: Portsmouth sign ex-Southend and Accrington players

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League Two side Portsmouth have signed striker Noel Hunt and defender Adam Buxton on one-year contracts.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Former Reading and Dundee United man Hunt, 33, was a free agent after leaving Southend, where he scored four goals in 22 appearances last campaign.
He has scored 71 goals in 341 league games in England and Scotland.
Full-back Buxton, 24, turned down a new contract at Accrington for whom he played 31 times last season, including in the League Two play-offs.
